            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "After applying black to the whole codebase I get errors like this \r\n```\r\nError compiling Cython file:\r\n------------------------------------------------------------\r\n...\r\n          |name| is optional, and may be the name of the file being\r\n          scanned or any other identifying string.\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        self.trace = 0\r\n\r\n        self.buffer = \"\"\r\n                      ^\r\n------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nCython/Plex/Scanners.py:92:22: str objects do not support coercion to unicode, use a unicode string literal instead (u'')\r\n```\r\nafter black changes `self.buffer = u''` to `self.buffer = \"\"`.\r\n\r\nI suspect this is because of the directive \r\n```\r\n# cython: language_level=3str\r\n```\r\ndoes that mean that we can't apply black because the assumptions of black about strings are not valid in cython with this directive ?",
