        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> I avoid contributing to projects that mandate either black or pre-commit. The former because it results in unreadable code\r\n\r\nI think that's exaggerating it. Yes, some code becomes less \"but I wanted it so\" when using an automatic code formatter. But from my experience, it's really rare that I'm so unhappy with the result that I consider it worth a manual change. Happens, ok. But even then, it's usually not too difficult to find a spelling on which me and the code formatter can agree. And that makes me rethink the way I've formatted the code, which is actually often a good thing.",
