            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "IMHO, if we want to start using black (or maybe rather blue), Cython 3.1 would be the time to start. We'd be ripping out a lot of Py2 related code at that point, which already makes backports to 3.0 difficult, because they'd probably require adding a Py2 implementation or making the code itself Py2 compatible. Code formatting differences won't add much to that.",
