        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Note that ruff is just another color of the bikeshed. Its main claim to fame is \"Introducing, the one and only! A rewrite of black, but written in rust and a lot faster! Also we support your choice of single quotes, if you like, the same way several black forks such as `blue` do\".\n\nIt was an intentional goal of ruff that there should be effectively no changes produced when reformatting black code using ruff. There are a small handful of minor differences. Nobody who wants a formatter will be overly concerned about whether to use black or ruff. Anyone who dislikes black is *exceedingly* unlikely to be appeased by ruff, though.",
